metadata.author: Frances Hodgson Burnett
metadata.description: When orphaned Mary Lennox arrives at Misselthwaite Manor, her uncles estate, everybody said she was the most disagreeable looking child ever seen. Depressed and withdrawn, Mary stumbles upon an arched doorway into an overgrown garden. She later discovers her pampered invalid cousin, tucked away in a dark room. Soon a charming journey into the magical secret garden begins
